features: FOLDABLE DISH RACK: A draining rack allows you to efficiently dry your dishes, mugs, pots and pans. Once done, it’s easy to fold and stow away so it doesn’t take counter space.
WELL MADE: Strong screws (not staples) hold the kitchen counter dish rack together and they’re easy to open or fold. And it’s not just functional, it looks real nice in your kitchen too.
28 SLOTS: You get 14 plate slots in each tier to fit a lot of dishes in your kitchen dish drying rack. Plates fit well in the upper tier, while mugs and smaller plates fit well in the lower one.
HIGH QUALITY BAMBOO: If you want a better option than ugly plastic or metal strainers, treat yourself to this bamboo dish rack for kitchen counter. Bamboo is sturdy, chic and good for the planet.
SAVE TIME: You can boycott wiping dishes dry. Just place them on this dishes drying rack and let the air do its work. The slats are properly spaced apart to allow the perfect amount of air flow.
12-MONTH WARRANTY: We stand behind our drying rack for a full 12 months. Should it break before, please contact us for your free replacement or full refund.
OUR MISSION: To create functional and beautiful products that you’ll love in your home. In addition to doing the job, our products will upgrade your decor.

Now having dishes in the sink really is no big deal. You simply wash ‘em, plunk ‘em on the dish rack and move on to the next thing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice versatile design and very sturdy
reviews.reviewText: I like this dish rack because it is made from bamboo versus plastic. It is very sturdy, the adjustable parts fold outward or inward as far or as little as you want them to go, depending on what you need to dry. There's an upper tier for larger items such as pans, plates, and bowls. The bottom tier folds out for smaller items like cups or utensils. I fold this bottom tier back in when I don't need to use it, and it takes up less space. If you have very limited counter space I would get something smaller. Easy to care for, has instructions included. I highly recommend this product.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and a great (larger) option than most!
reviews.reviewText: This replaced two Ikea drying racks that eventually got moldy. The two levels make it so easy to dry everything I need to, giving me plenty of space, and it easily folds up when you're done with it. I'll update later on how it holds up over time but for now, definitely a great buy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I like it, but...
reviews.reviewText: ... it needs a little attention before you use it. The basic construction is good, but the edges of the bamboo have not been eased. You'll need to sand them to keep splinters out of your fingers. Everything is tight. Too tight. It is hard to get unfolded. Then it is hard to fold back. A little candle wax on the opposing surfaces helps. This rack will need to be dried regularly as mold is a problem with bamboo that stays wet. On the plus side, I like the sturdiness, design, and slot size. I like that it can be folded, laid flat and used as a drying surface. I like that it can be put away, will not rust and doesn't wobble. I think it is worth the price.
